import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size()
    plt.hist(group_sizes, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of group sizes?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    group_sizes.plot(kind='bar')

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    group_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of people across groups?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_sizes = data.groupby(['group', 'person']).size().unstack()
    group_sizes.plot(kind='bar', stacked=False)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of group sizes for each name?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
